## 5. 🎯 Mocking dengan Mockery

### Basic Mock Expectations

#### `shouldReceive()` - Basic Setup
```php
$this->prakarsarepo->shouldReceive('getPrakarsa')
    ->once()  // Dipanggil tepat 1x
    ->andReturn($prakarsaMock);
```

#### Call Count Modifiers
```php
->once()              // Dipanggil tepat 1x
->twice()             // Dipanggil tepat 2x
->atLeast()->once()   // Dipanggil minimal 1x
->times(2)            // Dipanggil tepat 2x
->never()             // Tidak boleh dipanggil
```

#### Argument Matching
```php
// Exact argument
->shouldReceive('getPrakarsa')
    ->with("REF001", "123456")
    ->andReturn($prakarsa);

// Type checking
->shouldReceive('setProfilUsaha')
    ->with(Mockery::type('object'), Mockery::type('string'))
    ->andReturn($request);

// Closure/Callback matching
->shouldReceive('getPrakarsaHistory')
    ->with(Mockery::on(fn($filter) => $filter['norek'] === '123456'), Mockery::type('array'))
    ->andReturn([$prakarsa]);
```

#### Exception Handling
```php
// Throw exception
$this->eksternalservice->shouldReceive('kirimAkadSIKP')
    ->once()
    ->andThrow(new ThirdPartyServiceException("SIKP error"));

// Test expectation
$this->expectException(ThirdPartyServiceException::class);
```

#### Multiple Return Values
```php
$this->service->shouldReceive('method')
    ->andReturn($value1)
    ->andReturn($value2)
    ->andReturn($value3);
```

### Protected Method Mocking
Jika perlu mock protected methods:

```php
$service = $this->makeService();
$service->shouldAllowMockingProtectedMethods();

$service->shouldReceive('getPrakarsaHistory')
    ->once()
    ->andReturn([$prakarsa]);
```

