## 10. 🔄 Test Lifecycle

```php
class MyUsecaseTest extends TestCase
{
    // 1. SETUP: Called before each test
    protected function setUp(): void
    {
        parent::setUp();
        // Initialize mocks
        $this->repo = Mockery::mock(Repository::class);
    }
    
    // 2. TEST: Run test logic
    public function testSomething()
    {
        // ARRANGE
        $this->repo->shouldReceive('find')->andReturn($data);
        
        // ACT
        $result = $this->service->process();
        
        // ASSERT
        $this->assertTrue($result);
    }
    
    // 3. TEARDOWN: Called after each test
    protected function tearDown(): void
    {
        \Mockery::close();
        parent::tearDown();
    }
}

// Execution order:
// 1. setUp()
// 2. testSomething()
// 3. tearDown()
// (repeat for each test method)
```

